<br>
I know most of my guildies, me included, feel we're a success because we take less people into a place than the &quot;norm&quot; guild and rock the joint.  We're not 50+ strong.  I would say we've got about 25.  At any peek times, you can find 15 to 20 of us on.  <br>
<br>
I feel we're also successful because of all our friends outside if the guild.  We're out to make a positive impact on everything we do... even the wipes.  Heheh.<br>
<br>
We have the BEST leader there is, period, and no one could tell me otherwise.  *grins*  Antigo listens, demands, helps, comforts, yells, cries, and celebrates with the rest of his guild.  He definately pushes our limits as a guild and as individuals, but does it in a way that you are begging for more.<br>
<br>
I have known most of my guild for 25+ lvls now.  We know what we are able to do to help one another.  We know what our weaknesses and strengths are.<br>
<br>
I think I can sum it up into one sentance....  We are there for eachother in every way necessary.<br>
<br>
This is just me rambling on about my wonderful guild, but I hope it enlightens someone, if only to show you it all depends on your own views, needs, and desires.  Pick a guild that has the same values and go with it.  Make friends along the way, and most of all....<br>
<br>
HAVE FUN!!!!<br>
<br>
